reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect daily duffle
reviews.reviewText: I bought the medium in black after reading reviews that the large doesn't fit under flight seats. I needed a personal item, something that wouldn't make waves on a flight AND doubles as a reasonable gym bag/work bag. The medium is the bag for me.The vented shoe compartment is great for shoes or lunch. I love being able to toss my lunch in the bottom instead of a separate lunch bag because it's one less problem to grab in the morning. Not to mention when I bring gym shoes to work, the vents help from having the smell brew in the bag so it's insufferable.I love the lining of it. It's not all waterproof, but it's definitely more resistant than canvas. I've carried it through rain (not downpour) and my laptop made it to work just fine. And all the compartments do help to organize things for easy access.The only draw backs I've noticed is how the outer bottle pockets are difficult to use if over stuffed. Luckily I don't pack a rigid bottle when I fly so my flexible hair and makeup pouches easily fit there. The lack of laptop pocket is also sad, but that is clear in the description so I just live with my choice by packing mindfully when going places with my laptop. The last draw back is the lack of rigidity in the bag. I do love the flex in the top so I can stuff a weekend worth of clothes in the top, but if nothing is in the bottom it is hard to free stand.Even with these draw backs it's still a 5-star for me!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Stop hesitating and buy it!!
reviews.reviewText: This bag is seriously perfect. I’m the type of girl who always needs her skincare, makeup, hair care products, extra clothes, hygiene products, chargers, etc when I’m out of my house overnight. This duffel bag has been such a lifesaver and has saved me so much hassle when it comes to staying out and keeping my things organized. I tend to sleep over at my boyfriend’s house a lot and this has been my best friend. Even if I don’t bring a ton of items, I can store extra things in it that I might get when I’m out.This is definitely the perfect bag for any kind of travel and I know I’ll be using it for every trip here on out. It’s super high quality, has all the pockets you could ever need (including the amazing pocket for wet clothing), and is overall very pretty and sleek. Highly recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Really a 5 star!! I love this so much!!!
reviews.reviewText: I got this for a gym bag, but it has become my bag for everything. I love how much I can fit in this bag. I love the shoe compartment. I also love the small bag that comes with it. I love the lining on the inside. I also love that there is an inside pocket and the cord for charging through the bag. It does have a luggage strap which works great for airport travel. It is a soft shell bag so it does not stand up as pictured when not filled. The quality is great and is very easy to clean. This bag is water resistant so great for daily use. I love the outside side pockets! It is great for organizing items. The price for this item is amazing!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Ordered this last minute for a trip to use as my personal item. Overall it’s great - good quality, the material is sturdy and seems like it will hold up for travel well. As you can see in the picture, it fit well under the plane seat despite being packed pretty much as full as it can be.I wear size 11 shoes and was able to fit 2 pairs in the bottom compartment.Only two main complaints (that overall really aren’t that bad):1. The bag does not hold itself up in any way - it kind of looks like it would from the pictures but it is not a stiff material. It would be very squished if I didn’t use the bottom compartment2. The “water bottle holders” on the sides are about 4 inches too short so my metal water bottle kept falling out. Maybe a kids size bottle would stay in just fine.Overall it was worth the price for this trip and I can see myself using it again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful weekender bag
reviews.reviewText: Perfect! I had been wanting to get weekender bag for a while but competitors were so expensive. This one competes so well with the pricier brands. I love the color. There is so much space in this bag that I can fit almost everything I would need for a weekend trip in it. The shoe bags are super nice as well to make sure the bag and my clothes remain clean. I love the extra little bag that comes with it, perfect for my bathroom items. It's perfect for a carry-on option when flying.

reviews.reviewText: Amazing bag!!!! Love love loved it for my gym days has a lot of compartments and space. The usb port is a big perk and the bottom section love it you can have your shoes in the or sandals. Also great for traveling I have used it a couple times as well. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Gym/Travel/Overnight Bag
reviews.reviewText: I absolutely love this bag! It is the perfect size to fit everything you need for the gym like an outfit, towel, water bottle, shower supplies. I love how it comes with 2 bags to place your shoes in and a separate compartment on the bottom that doesn’t take away from the space inside! I also love how it came with a small accessory bag perfect to put travel sized products and the best part is you can connect a charging block inside the bag and charge your phone by connect a charging cable to the outside! This is perfect for a gym bag, overnight bag, or to even travel with! It could also be packed with a days worth of clothes, shower supplies and other necessities and kept in the car incase of emergency where you can’t make it home or are leaving for other reasons. I recommend this bag. It’s super durable and great quality!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not as pictured, but still serviceable
reviews.reviewText: The photos make this bag look like a matte, rigid neoprene-type of fabric that would keep its shape. It's not. The material is a shiny, unstructured polyester. However, the many pockets are useful, especially the zippered shoe compartment. If you're not picky about the material looking high-quality and don't care if the bag flops around, then it'll be a perfectly serviceable duffel. However, I am a little disappointed that the fabric is cheap-looking and it's a little annoying to be fighting the bag's lack of structure when packing. I will probably be on the lookout for a more quality bag in the future, but it'll do in the meantime.
